notes: TIPSY069-08, clv113 and TIPSY086-08 clv164 are both the same species, and different from TIPSY081-08 clv 126. These three are in the Genus Nemapogon of the Tineidae, one sp. will be coloacella, the other granella (the grain moth). They are notoriously difficult to separate by wing markings, and on the basis of these analyses I would not like to say which is which. I think we need to analyse more of this group, possibly obtaining granella from the CSL culture in Leeds, before deciding which is which. I will have a word with John Muggleton when I see him next and find out if he has a contact at CSL I could get in touch with. John used to work there when it was based in Slough.
